  "summary": "<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/10/wikipedia-turned-into-a-card-collecting-gacha-game.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Wikipedia turned into a card collecting gacha game\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Image-Sergey_Bogomyako-Shutterstock.jpg?fit=1080%2C720&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1080\" /></a><p>A new browser-based game turns Wikipedia entries into cards, combining card collecting with the acquisition of random knowledge.</p>\n<p>Instead of Pokémon or other creatures, <a href=\"http://wikigacha.com\">Wikipedia Gacha</a> lets you collect and battle with facts. New packs are available every sixty seconds, with bonus packs awarded for daily missions like sharing your results. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/10/wikipedia-turned-into-a-card-collecting-gacha-game.html\">Read the rest </a></p>",
